-- IBM to buy Israeli startup for $300 million: report
-- 
-- Mon Dec 31, 2007 5:55am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/31/us-xiv-ibm-idUSL3155914220071231

 

 JERUSALEM  (Reuters) - International Business Machines Corp ( IBM.N ) is in advanced talks to buy Israeli start-up XIV Information Systems for $300 million to $350 million, financial daily Globes reported on Monday. 

 XIV officials declined to comment. According to Globes, XIV has developed a system that replaces conventional storage technologies through the use of grid technology and less expensive hardware. (Reporting by Sergio Tjong-Alvares, Editing by Erica Billingham)